<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com<item><title><![CDATA[Massive Attack confirm death of guitarist Angelo Bruschini]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/music/2023/oct/24/massive-attack-confirm-death-of-guitarist-angelo-bruschini]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T15:52:10Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/cc9d3d03114649514b0d594f7062ee4a557f8fcf/0_50_3027_1816 /master/3027.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=a9eac6ec3da50b2135b593f71b254ff5&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Angelo Bruschini 于 2014 年在格拉斯顿伯里与 Massive Attack 一起表演&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;英国乐队 Massive Attack 领先向已去世 62 岁的“才华横溢且古怪”的吉他手 Angelo Bruschini 致敬。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Bruschini 帮助发展了布里斯托尔 Trip-hop 乐队独特的声音，并在该市的艺术摇滚乐队 The 中演奏吉他。蓝色飞机公司在夏天透露他患有癌症。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他写道：“医院的专家两次对我说‘祝你好运’，因为我患了肺癌，我想我完蛋了！度过了美好的生活，见过这个世界很多很多次，遇到了很多很棒的人，但大门即将关闭，我想我会写一本书。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Massive Attack 在 X（前 Twitter）上说道：“A才华横溢而又古怪的人才。无法量化您对大规模攻击经典的贡献。我们多么幸运能够一起分享这样的生活。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他们在 X 和 Instagram 上发布了这位吉他手的黑白照片，称他们对失去这位吉他手感到“震惊”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;布鲁斯基尼的妻子杰西卡·梅里特在 Facebook 上写道：“我非常悲伤地宣布，我美丽的丈夫安杰洛·布鲁斯基尼于 2023 年 10 月 23 日凌晨 12 点 15 分去世。它来自一种罕见的侵袭性癌症——多形性癌。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她说，他一直是一位“至始至终的绅士”，人们会因为他的“疯狂”幽默感和音乐才能而被人们铭记。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;布鲁斯基尼在录音室和路上演奏了《Massive Attack》。他将被铭记的歌曲之一是《Mezzanine》专辑中的《Angel》，正如一位评论家所描述的那样，这张专辑是由“吉他墙”驱动的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在他们的 Facebook 页面上，The Blue Airplanes自称是“布里斯托尔历史最悠久的乐队，公认对 REM 和 Radiohead 产生影响的艺术摇滚机构”，他说：“我们悲痛地宣布我们的兄弟安杰洛·布鲁斯基尼 (Angelo Bruschini) 去世了。在这个困难的时刻，我们的思念与他的家人同在。 Rest In Peace Ange x”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乐队发布了一张他在布里斯托尔港口边阳光明媚的日子里演奏的照片。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尽管得到了诊断结果，Bruschini 表示他不会在过去的几个月里，除了演奏音乐之外，他还继续对保守党政府进行猛烈抨击。球迷们记得他是一个优秀的人，也是一位才华横溢的音乐家。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;西英格兰大学布里斯托尔分校的历史和遗产教授史蒂夫·普尔 (Steve Poole) 说：“最后一次看到他在飞机上演奏是在 12 月，迷失在音乐，并兴高采烈地鼓励随机人群帮助他用吉他弹奏《打破我的心》的和弦。很遗憾我们再也见不到他了。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;苏珊娜·菲茨杰拉德 (Suzanne Fitzgerald) 说：“在安杰洛与 Ensign 唱片公司签约期间，我一直与他一起工作。但在此之前，我在 80 年代中期在布里斯托尔的许多舞台上看到他卓越的吉他演奏后，就很欣赏他了。他在舞台上和唱片上的表现都非常出色。他也非常有魅力，而且很有才华，适合共事。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 25 Oct 2023 02:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[US man left out of Russia prisoner swap says diplomats ‘signed death warrant’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/oct/24/paul-whelan-russia-prisoner-swap-interview]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T13:59:41Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/23c1b9eebc7fffa7963cf2fe7525e69d733decd5/0_126_3500_2101 /master/3500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=fb22376a656fc56430c95126517ff841&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Paul Whelan（右）于 2020 年被判处 16 年监禁。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;退休人员近五年前，一名美国海军陆战队员因间谍指控在俄罗斯被监禁，俄罗斯称这些指控是虚假的，他告诉美国高级外交官，过去两次白宫与克里姆林宫的囚犯交换中被忽略，最多是“给他背上了一个靶子”。&lt;/ p>; &lt;p>;在&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cnn.com/2023/10/24/politics/paul-whelan-blinken-cnn-interview/index.html&quot;>;CNN 的评论中&lt;/a >; 在周二发表的文章中，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/dec/08/paul-whelan-Russia-brittney-griner-prisoner-swap&quot;>;Paul Whelan&lt;/a>; 说道他在 8 月份与安东尼·布林肯通电话时告诉美国国务卿“直截了当地说，第一次把我留在这里，就给我的背上留下了一个靶子”。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关： &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/oct/24/us-state-senator-arrested-hong-kong-pistol&quot;>;美国州参议员在香港被捕孔在随身包里的手枪&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“第二次把我留在这里基本上签署了死刑令，”惠兰在一次电话交谈中告诉网络。星期五。惠兰在位于莫尔多维亚的偏远战俘营中发表讲话时，回忆起他还告诉布林肯，“除非他们把我抓回来，否则未来可能会非常具有挑战性，特别是考虑到我的年龄以及从健康和安全角度来看我们必须做的工作” ”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;53 岁的惠兰表示，他仍然相信美国会继续努力释放他。但他告诉美国有线电视新闻网，他担心自己会因为“其他地缘政治问题”而被遗忘。他没有具体说明他是否指的是&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/israel-hamas-war&quot;>;战争&lt;/a>;哈马斯于 10 月 7 日袭击以色列后爆发，引发了另一场重大全球冲突，&lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/ Russia+ukraine&quot;>;俄罗斯去年入侵乌克兰。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我认为每个人都在努力做正确的事情，而且我知道这会在某个时候结束，”惠兰说。 “我不知道要花多长时间。但有人向我保证，我不会被抛在这儿。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;俄罗斯当局在莫斯科的一家酒店逮捕了来自密歇根州的企业安全主管惠兰，指控他是情报人员- 采集操作。尽管美国认为惠兰被错误拘留，但他还是在 2020 年被判处 16 年监禁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乔·拜登白宫去年与俄罗斯协调了两次囚犯交换，让这位篮球明星获得了&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/sport/2023/apr/27/brittney-griner- Russia-arrest-press-conference&quot;>;布兰妮·格林纳&lt;/a>;和海军陆战队老兵&lt;a href=&quot;https: //www.theguardian.com/world/2022/apr/27/us- Russia-prisoner-exchange-trevor-reed-moscow-yaroshenko&quot;>;特雷弗·里德&lt;/a>;回到美国以换取俄罗斯军火商维克托·布特和毒贩康斯坦丁·亚罗申科。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;美国官员表示，俄罗斯拒绝将惠兰纳入这些交易。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Griner 于 12 月获释后，惠兰的兄弟大卫，&lt;a href =&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/dec/08/paul-whelan-rusia-brittney-griner-prisoner-swap&quot;>;说&lt;/a>;拜登政府做出了“正确的决定”一名篮球运动员因携带少量大麻油进入俄罗斯而被监禁后返回。但大卫·惠兰表示，他无法想象他的兄弟“此时此刻有任何希望政府能够就他的自由进行谈判”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“很明显，美国政府不会像俄罗斯政府那样为保罗做出让步。”惠兰，”大卫·惠兰说。 “因此，保罗将继续被囚禁，直到这种情况发生变化。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;据美国有线电视新闻网 (CNN) 报道，在弗拉基米尔·普京领导的国家“未能在这是今年早些时候提出要约的实质性方式”。美国有线电视新闻网 (CNN) 表示，国务院周一告诉该网络，它仍然致力于“带保罗回家”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;保罗·惠兰在周二发表的声明中表示，他认为拜登授权是“一个错误”美国“尽快”交换亚罗申科和布特。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;不过，他表示，他知道俄罗斯已寻求释放在德国被判处终身监禁的俄罗斯前上校瓦迪姆·克拉西科夫(Vadim Krasikov)谋杀罪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;惠兰说，他的战俘营的条件不断恶化。热水系统和散热器需要维修。据他介绍，监狱商店不再出售新鲜水果或蔬菜，而且由于俄罗斯经济低迷，罐头食品也已停产。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们希望一些维修工作……能很快得到处理。” ，”他说。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 25 Oct 2023 02:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[US bodyguard sentenced to prison in Dubai over fan ‘slap’ appeals for help]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/oct/24/bodyguard-trey-songz-prison-dubai-uae]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T16:11:48Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/e5308677f7086598a486fba1a94ea19589294da5/0_66_805_483 /master/805.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=ae4196ca0f8a85cda01ba50bf3537472&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;康奈尔·惠特菲尔德（左）和特雷·宋兹。惠特菲尔德已联系他的美国国会代表寻求帮助。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;一名在 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/ 被判入狱的迈阿密保镖的家人lists/tag/world/dubai&quot;>;迪拜&lt;/a>;在介入阻止一名歌迷接近 R&amp;B 歌手 Trey Songz 后寻求帮助。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;康奈尔·惠特菲尔德 (Cornell Whitfield) 在被指控三月份，当他们离开豪华的朱美拉五棕榈酒店时，他们掌掴了一名约旦男子。这是该组织 &lt;a href=&quot;https://detained-in-dubai.prowly.com/267265-family-of-bodyguard-faceing-year-in-dubai-prison-appeal-for-support&quot;>; 的说法被拘留在迪拜，&lt;/a>;该机构为阿拉伯联合酋长国的外国人提供法律援助。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Whitfield，40 岁，曾担任 Lil&#39; Kim、达拉斯牛仔队角卫 Trevon Diggs 和旧金山 49 人队外接手迪博·塞缪尔 (Deebo Samuel)。惠特菲尔德表示，当他将自己置于真名特雷梅因·内弗森(Tremaine Neverson)的歌手和这名男子之间时，他是在“尽自己的职责”。惠特菲尔德的律师通过迪拜拘留中心指控这名男子“喝醉了，行为具有威胁性和攻击性” ”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;据报道，该男子索要 6 万美元才能撤销指控。该组织表示，惠特菲尔德原以为迪拜法院系统会宣判他无罪，因为他说自己的行为是出于自卫，并且保持了克制。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“他只是在做自己的工作，没想到这名男子会这么做。”怀特菲尔德的表弟萨雷娜·乔治 (Sarena George) 告诉迪拜拘留所，考虑到他的行为就是他的行为，请进行投诉。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;乔治引用了酒店保安、监控录像和目击者的证据。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;但当惠特菲尔德八月返回迪拜时，他被捕并被判处一年监禁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“如果保镖可以因为保护客户而入狱，那么名人真的应该支持迪拜吗？”迪拜拘留中心首席执行官拉达·斯特林 (Radha Stirling) 的倡导者兼律师写道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;斯特林补充道：“外国人被当地人视为猎物，他们知道他们会为琐碎或虚假的案件支付大笔费用。掉了。当地人将迪拜的警察部队变成了敲诈勒索的工具，这对游客来说风险极大。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;叠叠乐形状的朱美拉五棕榈酒店已成为美国明星的热门目的地。据报道，碧昂斯今年早些时候在那里举办了一场长达一小时的音乐会，据报道获得了 2400 万美元的报酬年。她因在一个对性别和性权利有限制性法律的国家演出而受到批评。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Whitfield 已欠下超过 35,000 美元的法律债务。他的家人已联系佛罗里达州国会女议员 Frederica Wilson 以及美国国务院寻求帮助。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;他的母亲 Marysia Whitfield 说：“我们真的希望法官至少推翻​​监禁判决。”&lt; /p>; &lt;p>;她说：“如果他确实犯了罪，那是一回事，但他只是在做他的工作。他没有自找麻烦。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;对 Whitfield 的指控以及随后的金钱要求似乎反映了 21 岁美国学生 Elizabeth Polanco De Los Santos 的经历。因利用机场保安寻求帮助而被判处 12 个月监禁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Polanco 是布朗克斯区雷曼学院商业艺术专业的学生，​​据报道，她正在经过迪拜机场时，机场海关官员告诉她要采取行动。波兰科说，她拍了拍其中一名妇女的手臂，请求帮助重新戴上该设备。海关官员声称波兰科一直在“攻击和侮辱”。后来，在海关工作人员对法院判处的 2,772 美元罚款的宽大处理提出上诉后，她被暂时禁止离开该国。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;美国驻迪拜大使馆和美国国会议员里奇·托雷斯 (Ritchie Torres) 被美国驻迪拜大使馆逮捕后，波兰科于 10 月被释放。迪拜被拘留者说，涉及其中。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 25 Oct 2023 02:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Pope accepts resignation of Polish bishop after gay orgy scandal in diocese]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/24/pope-accepts-resignation-polish-bishop-grzegorz-kaszak-gay-orgy-scandal-diocese]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T18:33:57Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/518fa871bdb36ae14172d7cd21a2c0de3df76126/0_0_2327_1397 /master/2327.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=b4190f480184b9002d469b091b06b08b&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;教皇方济各在梵蒂冈圣彼得广场举行每周一次的公开接见。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;教皇已接受一名波兰主教的辞职，该主教的教区因神父公寓内涉及一名男性性工作者的同性恋狂欢以及之前涉及其神职人员的暴力事件的报道而震动。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;梵蒂冈没有给出格热戈日·卡扎克 (Grzegorz Kaszak) 辞去西南部索斯诺维茨教区负责人的原因 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com/international/lists/tag/world/poland&quot;>;波兰&lt;/a>;。他现年 59 岁，距离 75 岁的正常退休年龄还差好几年。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但在他的一名牧师因涉嫌在他的公寓组织狂欢而受到刑事调查后，他的教区成为了人们关注的焦点。在 Dąbrowa Górnicza，涉及一名男性性工作者。波兰媒体报道称，性爱派对的一名参与者因服用过量勃起功能障碍药物而晕倒。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一名检察官表示，这名牧师涉嫌“未能向生命处于危险之中的人提供帮助”据称，他们试图阻止护理人员进入公寓。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这并不是该教区第一次涉及神职人员的事件成为头条新闻。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;2010 年，时任索斯诺维茨代理教区长据称，神学院在一家同性恋俱乐部发生了扭打，但即使在波兰媒体报道此事后，他仍被允许继续工作一年多。据人民行动党通讯社报道，罗马教廷最终介入并彻底解散了该神学院。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;2023 年 3 月，一名 26 岁执事的尸体被发现，伤势疑似他杀。当地检察官称，他被一名 40 岁的牧师杀害，后者随后自杀。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在周二的一份声明中，卡扎克表示，他已在 9 月 29 日的一封信中请求教皇让他辞职。 。他感谢教区的神父和修女，并请求“大家原谅我作为人的局限性”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;卡扎克在短暂担任梵蒂冈第二号人物后，于 2009 年被当时的教皇本笃十六世任命为主教。家族办公室。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该教区确认参与所谓狂欢的神父为托马斯·Z(Tomasz Z)，该教区在很大程度上证实了媒体报道，称外部调查委员会得出的结论是，他犯下了“非常严重违反道德规范的行为”。 ”，以及他作为牧师的义务。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;卡萨克于 9 月 21 日解除了该牧师的所有职务，并启动了内部规范审判，其结果可能导致解除神职或世俗化，根据教区网站上的一份声明。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;波兰检察官尚未对这名神父提出指控。波兰媒体援引他在丑闻爆发后不久发表的声明，否认他阻止医护人员进入他的公寓，并质疑“狂欢”的定义。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我认为这明显是对教堂的攻击，包括神职人员和信徒，以羞辱其地位、任务和使命，”该神父在每天通过电子邮件发送给《Gazeta Wyborcza》的声明中援引他的话说。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 25 Oct 2023 02:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Finland recovers ship’s anchor close to damaged Baltic Sea pipeline]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/24/finland-recovers-ships-anchor-close-to-damaged-baltic-sea-pipeline]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T17:06:09Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/3419eb777c889923d3cfa5d0a5ee99cebaf22280/0_276_4928_2957 /master/4928.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=169524cac8a6ba15f86cae2a75333f88&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;芬兰 Balticconnector 海洋天然气管道的压缩站。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;芬兰调查人员发现了一个波罗的海天然气管道附近的大型船舶锚&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/10/undersea-pipeline-damage-appears-to-be-deliberate-芬兰中央刑事警察局 (KRP) 周二表示，该锚重 6 吨，严重受损，正在确定是否来自中国集装箱船。缺少一个尖头，是用海军起重机从海底吊起的。在破裂的管道两侧发现了很深的拖痕。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该国国家调查局 (NBI)，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/ oct/20/chinese-ship-is-focus-of-investigation-into-damated-pipeline-finland-says&quot;>;上周称调查重点&lt;/a>;是悬挂香港国旗的中资公司NewNew Polar Bear周二在赫尔辛基告诉记者，这艘集装箱船缺少前锚。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;b39e2be0bcca6c5b2ca0bede991f85047bb9683f&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/ b39e2be0bcca6c5b2ca0bede991f85047bb9683f/0_52_719_719/500.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;芬兰海军回收的锚。&quot; width=&quot;500&quot; height=&quot;500&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;芬兰海军在天然气管道附近回收的锚。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：NBI/Reuters&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;国调局表示，已努力联系该船，该船的活动与管道损坏情况密切相关，但到目前为止尚未成功，并补充说，调查现在的重点是损坏是否是故意的。&lt;国调局局长罗宾·拉尔多 (Robin Lardot) 表示：“接下来的问题是关于这是否是故意、疏忽、航海技术不佳，这就是我们要了解所发生的事情是否有动机的地方。现阶段回答这个问题还为时过早。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;赫尔辛基 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/10/undersea-pipeline-damage-appears- to-be-deliberate-says-finland&quot;>;确认 10 月 11 日，芬兰和爱沙尼亚之间的 Balticconnector 天然气管道和并行 Estlink 数据通信电缆遭到损坏，两天前，运营商因气温突然下降而关闭了管道调查人员随后表示，他们怀疑损坏是由“机械而非爆炸”的“外力”造成的。国家安全情报部门表示，“不能排除”国家行为者的参与。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian .com/world/2023/oct/20/chinese-ship-is-focus-of-investigation-into-damaging-pipeline-finland-says&quot;>;芬兰表示，中国船只是受损管道调查的重点&lt;/a>; &lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;芬兰&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/apr/04/finland-nato-member-brussels-ceremony&quot;>;今年早些时候加入北约俄罗斯入侵乌克兰后，跨大西洋联盟放弃了长期的不结盟政策一年后，跨大西洋联盟承诺，如果管道损坏是因破坏行为造成的，将采取“团结、坚决的应对措施”。&lt;/p>; &lt; Balticconnector 的运营商表示，修复管道至少需要五个月的时间，并且最早要到 2024 年 4 月才能再次投产。芬兰约 5% 的能源供应依赖天然气。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-interactive=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/embed/iframe-wrapper/0.1/boot.js&quot; data- canonical-url=&quot;https://interactive.guim.co.uk/uploader/embed/2023/10/balticconnector-map/giv-13425x83Idw6kCBeA/&quot; data-alt=&quot;Balticconnector 管道图&quot;>; &lt;a href=&quot;https ://interactive.guim.co.uk/uploader/embed/2023/10/balticconnector-map/giv-13425x83Idw6kCBeA/&quot;>;互动&lt;/a>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;周二，瑞典首相乌尔夫克里斯特森表示，瑞典和爱沙尼亚之间波罗的海下第二条电信电缆的损坏是“故意的”，但拒绝透露细节。克里斯特森告诉记者：“从今天开始，我们不会比这更精确。”瑞典海军告诉公共广播公司 SVT，在附近的海底发现了踪迹，但补充道：“我们不知道知道这是故意还是意外。”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;2b01032d55adb7cca24e7acf76dada776b8ab2d0&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/2b01032d55adb7cca24e7acf76dada776b8ab2d0/69_0_1715_10 29/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;这张未注明日期的讲义图片中描绘了连接芬兰和爱沙尼亚的一条受损的波罗的海连接器天然气管道。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;这张未注明日期的讲义图片中描绘了一条连接芬兰和爱沙尼亚的受损的波罗的海连接器天然气管道。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：芬兰边防卫队/路透社&lt; /span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;北约秘书长延斯·斯托尔滕贝格周二表示，联盟成员国拥有来自波罗的海的“数万公里”的海底互联网电缆、电力电缆、天然气管道和石油管道斯托尔滕贝格说：“当然，这些类型的海底关键基础设施很脆弱。”他补充说，北约在事件发生后加强了在波罗的海的巡逻，正在与私营部门合作，该联盟“拥有大部分关键基础设施”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在去年发生一系列仍未解决的爆炸导致破裂后，该联盟于 6 月启动了一个新的海底管道和电缆保护中心&lt;a href=&quot;https: //www.theguardian.com/business/2022/sep/27/nord-stream-1-2-pipelines-leak-baltic-sabotage-fears&quot;>;输送俄罗斯天然气的四条北溪管道中的三条&lt;/a>;到西欧。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 25 Oct 2023 02:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Iceland PM joins 25,000 people for first full-day women’s strike in 48 years]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/24/iceland-prime-minister-joins-womens-strike-katrin-jakobsdottir]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T17:04:43Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/30ffc4e48f1af9ee323e4744860302f326da8524/0_29_2048_1229 /master/2048.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=93fd1b50aefdee50233f1dcb6dcef9ce&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;冰岛妇女罢工&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;冰岛总理表示，她希望实现全面罢工到 2030 年，她的国家将实现性别平等，她与 25,000 名妇女和非二元性别人士一起进行全天罢工，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/23/icelands- 48 年来首次全天女性罢工旨在缩小薪酬差距&quot;>;近半个世纪以来首次&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在外面讲话周二在雷克雅未克市中心举行的大型集会开始前，卡特琳·雅各布斯多蒂尔在她的办公室表示，世界在性别平等方面进展缓慢，但冰岛正在尽最大努力解决围绕性别工资差距、性别问题的“巨大问题”。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她告诉《卫报》：“我的梦想是我们将在 2030 年之前实现[实现完全性别平等]，但我知道这需要付出很多努力。我们一直在针对这两个问题对立法进行修改，希望我们能够继续前进。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;引用联合国的估计，按照目前的进展速度，需要 300 年的时间才能实现这一目标。为了实现这一目标，Jakobsdóttir 补充道：“全球女性必须等待 300 年才能实现完全平等，这是不可接受的。”&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt; a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/live/2023/oct/24/iceland-womens-strike-gender-pay-gap-europe-latest-updates&quot;>;冰岛首次全天妇女罢工48年来旨在缩小薪酬差距 - 欧洲生活&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;罢工的组织者 - 48年来首次全天罢工 - 表示该行动引起了广泛的关注冰岛各地学校和幼儿园关闭，只有一家银行继续营业。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;至少 25,000 名女性聚集在雷克雅未克市中心，呼吁缩小该国的工资差距 – 女性平均收入比男性低 21%根据冰岛统计局的数据，到 2022 年，男性将成为男性，并结束基于性别的暴力和性暴力，这种暴力影响了冰岛 40% 的女性一生。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在全国各地的城镇，包括胡萨维克、阿库雷里和 Sauðárkrókur，还有数千名妇女参加了抗议活动，口号是 &lt;em>;Kallarðu þetta jafnrétti？ （&lt;/em>;你管这叫平等？）。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但最大的活动是在雷克雅未克市中心的一座小山 Arnarhóll，在 1975 年第一次全天妇女罢工的地点附近举行。拥有大型音乐节的活力和人群。人群中有朋友、家人和同事参加，许多人举着标语牌，为扬声器欢呼，并与表演者一起唱歌。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;1975 年罢工的颂歌 Áfram Stelpur（前进女孩）最初由激进妇女运动红袜子乐队演唱，被吼叫。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;e454e7f3f82d8d0c436373bd4170335f6b051e31&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/e454e7f3f82d8d0c436373bd4170335f6b051e31/0_27 3_8192_4916/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;人们穿过冰岛在雷克雅未克举行妇女罢工期间聚集。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;冰岛各地的人们聚集在雷克雅未克的妇女罢工期间。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Arni Torfason/AP&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt; /figure>; &lt;p>;第一次妇女罢工给冰岛带来了重大变革，包括成立妇女政党、妇女联盟，以及选出世界上第一位女性民选总统。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但雅各布斯多蒂尔表示，尽管世界将冰岛视为性别平等方面的世界领先者，但“冰岛妇女非常清楚，我们在处理性别工资差距、性别暴力、性暴力和骚扰方面仍然存在巨大问题” .&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她补充说，她的政府致力于推动进一步的改革来解决这些问题。 “我们的经验是，性别平等不仅是正确的事情——显然是正确的事情——而且对经济和社会也有好处，”总理说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“显然，世界做得还不够，”她说，并补充道：“我们当中很少有女性世界领导人，[而且]我们在过去几年中失去了一些人。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;罢工的级别支持。与该国第一夫人雅各布斯多蒂尔 (Jakobsdóttir) 一起，作家伊丽莎·里德 (Eliza Reid) 分享了她的外出信息，其中表示她不会回复电子邮件，因为她正在罢工。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/24/power-of-the-masses-the-day-icelands-women-went-on-strike -and-changed-history&quot;>;“群众的力量”：冰岛妇女罢工改变历史的那一天&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“这是第七次罢工，但也是第一次自 1975 年以来，这种全天罢工一直在发生，当时 90% 的冰岛女性请了一天假，其结果多年来引起了整个社会的共鸣，”她写道。但是，她补充道：“近半个世纪过去了，平等仍远未实现，因此谨此提醒。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她的丈夫、总统 Guðni Th. Jóhannesson 也表达了他的支持，他在社交媒体上写道：“他们的平等行动让冰岛社会变得更好，并且至今仍在继续。”罢工涵盖了有偿和无偿工作，让父亲们全权负责家务和儿童保育。与此同时，企业和服务机构被迫雇用男性员工，或者关闭。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在雷克雅未克的一家便利店，只有男性在工作。一家餐厅试图通过聘请男性名人担任服务员来缓解这种情况。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而，有人担心是否每个想要罢工的人都能做到。冰岛妇女权利协会 (IWRA) 最初成立于 1907 年，旨在争取投票权，其主席 Tatjana Latinovic 表示：“我们关心的是，我们希望每个想要投票权的人参与将会参与——包括女性外籍工人。我们向雇主施加压力，要求他们不要惩罚罢工员工，并鼓励女性罢工。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她说，冰岛有 39,000 名外国女性，约占冰岛女性总人口的 18%。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在雷克雅未克，游行活动于上午 9 点开始，人们进行了一场轻快的晨间散步，参加罢工的学前教育教师、学生、市政工作人员、活动人士和参加 1975 年最初妇女罢工的妇女也加入其中 – – 在 Tjörnin 周围52 岁的 Sigridur Björg Tomasdottir 是雷克雅未克附近一个市政府的公关人员，她穿着鸟纹棉服，戴着手套，在冰点以上的温度下保持温暖，她说她认识的大多数女性都在罢工。她十几岁的孩子也计划参加，因为学校关闭了，因为学校大部分老师都是女性。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;42 岁的学前班老师 Steinunn Sigurgeirsdottir 与她的同事和老板一起参加了步行活动。她说，幼儿园已经关闭，但两名男性员工正在工作，有任务要做。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“对于女性来说，团结在一起很重要，”她说。 “冰岛有句俗话，&lt;em>;konur eru konum bestar &lt;/em>;（女人最适合女人）。”她说，她的职业以女性为主，工资很低。 “我正在争取对老师的更多尊重。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一名女性，美国空乘人员和工会代表，专程前往冰岛参加罢工，为工会的工资谈判获取建议和灵感。 53 岁的梅丽莎·奥斯本 (Melissa Osborne) 来自亚利桑那州，她说：“冰岛女性和她们的平等让我深受启发。美国有很多东西值得学习。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 25 Oct 2023 01:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta sued by 33 states over claims youth mental health endangered by Instagram]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/oct/24/instagram-lawsuit-meta-sued-teen-mental-health-us]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T16:34:06Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/6e6565d24e1cd516911f95e47fad1c63f881b310/0_0_7000_4200 /master/7000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=2fa85308f5bd884b1fa2b432d7c0be6d&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;元徽标&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;美国数十个州正在起诉 Meta Platforms 及其 Instagram 部门，指控他们社交媒体平台的成瘾性加剧了青少年心理健康危机。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周二，包括加利福尼亚州和伊利诺伊州在内的 33 个州向加利福尼亚州奥克兰联邦法院提起诉讼，Meta 表示，还运营 Facebook，多次误导公众了解其平台的重大危险，并故意诱导幼儿和青少年上瘾和强迫性地使用社交媒体。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Meta 利用强大且前所未有的技术来吸引、参与and ultimately ensnare youth and teens,” the complaint said. “Its motive is profit.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The lawsuit seeks a variety of remedies, including substantial civil penalties.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Meta said that it had sought to make teens safe online.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We&#39;re disappointed that instead of working productively with companies across the industry to create clear, age-appropriate standards for the many apps teens use, the attorneys general have chosen this path,” Meta said in an email statement.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Much of the focus on Meta stems from the release of documents in 2021 that revealed Meta had data showing that Instagram, which began as a photo-sharing app, was addictive and worsens body image issues for some teen girls.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The lawsuit alleges that Meta strives to ensure that young people spend as much time as possible on social media despite knowing that teenage brains are susceptible to the need for approval in the form of “likes” from other users about their content. Meta deceptively denied publicly that its social media was harmful, the lawsuit said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Nine other states are expected to file similar lawsuits on Tuesday, bringing the total number of states suing to 42.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Menlo Park, California, company and other social media companies already face hundreds of lawsuits brought on behalf of children and school districts raising similar claims.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 25 Oct 2023 00:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Trump’s former fixer Michael Cohen to testify at civil fraud trial – live]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2023/oct/24/trumps-former-fixer-michael-cohen-to-testify-at-civil-trial-live]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T16:19:10Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/6df0d12bf4f91189adce92610ca0c3e3590c26ff/0_60_1800_1081/master/1800.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=f073aa819e3490f7d8bd52a94b81c54e&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Michael Cohen, former Trump lawyer, is due in court to testify against his ex-boss.&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Wed, 25 Oct 2023 00:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[China removes two key figures from office in major leadership reshuffle]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/24/china-removes-two-key-figures-from-office-in-major-leadership-reshuffle-li-shangfu-qin-gang]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T15:43:32Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/796f3146d984c52caaefecd9f4f3f964a74bfcc8/0_251_4757_2854/master/4757.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=9cf41b717b26520a4584650781576be8&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Qin Gang (left) and Li Shangfu (right) in Beijing in March after being elected. &lt;/div>;&lt;p>;China has removed the defence minister, Li Shangfu, and ousted ex-foreign minister Qin Gang from its cabinet, according to state media, in a major reshuffle of top leadership.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The news came after months of speculation about the country&#39;s cabinet, including confusion over the abrupt removal of Qin from office in July without explanation and the months-long absence of Li from public view.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Both Qin and Li are believed by experts to have been personally selected for their roles by the president, Xi Jinping.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;State broadcaster CCTV announced the removals in its regular evening bulletin on Tuesday, but did not offer reasons for the ministers&#39; fall from grace.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;No replacement for Li as defence minister was announced.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Previously it had been reported that the US government believed Li was under investigation and had been stripped of his ministerial duties, but China had refused to comment on the matter.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Li travelled to Russia in August to attend a security conference near Moscow on 15 August. Two days later, the government of Belarus released handout photographs of Li meeting with the Belarusian president, Alexander Lukashenko, in Minsk. But since then he has vanished from public view.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Li&#39;s confirmed removal means there is no apparent host for China&#39;s regional security dialogue next week, the Xiangshan forum, which is due to be attended by representatives from the US Department of Defense.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Experts said Tuesday&#39;s announcement deepened the recent uncertainty around China&#39;s top leadership.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Neil Thomas, Chinese politics fellow at the Asia Society Policy Institute, said the recent upheaval “hints at severe deficiencies in the vetting process for top officials at the 20th party congress last year, possibly due to lower-level officials not wanting to push back against Xi&#39;s preferred candidates”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But the removal of Li and Qin is “unlikely to significantly undermine (Xi&#39;s) political authority, as neither was part of his true inner circle”, Thomas said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Their purge reinforces to other officials the importance of retaining Xi&#39;s favour.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As well as being removed as defence minister, Li has also lost his position on the state council, China&#39;s cabinet.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Qin, who was removed as foreign minister by Beijing&#39;s top lawmaking body after just 207 days in the job, has now also been stripped of his cabinet position.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;He was replaced by Wang Yi, a veteran diplomat who served as foreign minister before Qin and who outranked him in the Chinese government hierarchy.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;CCTV also announced on Tuesday that science and technology minister, Wang Zhigang, and finance minister, Liu Kun, had been removed from their posts.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;They will be replaced by current ministry of science and technology party secretary, Yin Hejun, and finance ministry party secretary, Lan Fo&#39;an, respectively.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Adam Ni, publisher of the China Neican newsletter, said the dismissals showed “elite politics at play”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Leadership instability continues unabated despite the cementing of paramount power by Xi,” he said, adding “all those below Xi with the exception of very few are subjected to quick falls from power”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“They can be picked and they can be discarded,” Ni said.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 24 Oct 2023 23:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Catastrophic’: bird flu reaches Antarctic for the first time]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/oct/24/catastrophic-penguins-and-seals-at-risk-as-bird-flu-reaches-antarctic-aoe]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T14:37:48Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c5f7266e88ec18aba5a5b3b138f91adfaadc7e98/0_328_5129_3079/master/5129.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=4826d0e0a9024124d8287477dadae4c1&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Brown skua and gentoo penguin on Cuverville Island, Antarctica.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Avian flu has reached the Antarctic, raising concerns for isolated populations of penguins and seals that have never been exposed to the deadly H5N1 virus before. The full impact of the virus&#39;s arrival is not yet known, but scientists are raising concerns about possible “catastrophic breeding failure” of the region&#39;s fragile wildlife populations.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The virus was found in populations of a scavenging bird called brown skua on Bird Island, which is part of the British overseas territory of South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands. These migratory birds probably brought it with them from South America where bird flu is widespread and has already killed &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.scar.org/scar-news/eg-bamm-news/awhn-news/avian-flu/&quot;>;an estimated&lt;/a>; 500,000 seabirds and 20,000 sea lions in Chile and Peru alone.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The current outbreak of the highly infectious variant of H5N1 – which started in 2021 – is estimated to have killed millions of wild birds. Researchers have long been concerned about its potential impact on Antarctic wildlife, because many species are found nowhere else in the world, and are not known to have been exposed to bird flu viruses before.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Researchers &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bas.ac.uk/polar-operations/sites-and-facilities/facility/bird-island/&quot;>;from the British Antarctic Survey (BAS)&lt;/a>; took swabs of the birds when they found unexplained mortality and sent them for testing in the UK.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Ashley Bennison, the BAS science manager for Bird Island, said: “This is a particularly sad event to confirm. We will continue to monitor the species on the island as best as we can and keep the science going, but we are unsure of the full impact at the moment.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Bird Island is considered one of the planet&#39;s &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.bas.ac.uk/polar-operations/sites-and-facilities/facility/bird-island/&quot;>;richest wildlife sites&lt;/a>;, home to many endangered bird species as well as 50,000 pairs of breeding penguins and 65,000 pairs of fur seals. The island lies just off the north-west tip of South Georgia, about 600 miles south-east of the Falkland Islands.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/oct/20/wild-birds-gain-immunity-to-avian-flu-in-encouraging-sign-amid-deadly-outbreak&quot;>;Wild birds gain immunity to avian flu in &#39;encouraging sign&#39; amid deadly outbreak&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;A &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.scar.org/library/science-4/life-sciences/antarctic-wildlife-health-network-awhn/5973-risk-assessment-avian-influenza/file/&quot;>;risk assessment&lt;/a>; on the impacts of bird flu reaching the continent, published by Scientific Committee on Antarctic Research, said fur seals, sea lions, skuas and gulls were the most at risk, followed by penguins, birds of prey, sheathbills and giant petrels.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Dr Meagan Dewar, the chair of the Antarctic Wildlife Health Network – who was the lead author of the report – said that the disease could result in “catastrophic breeding failure” in the region, with a “devastating impact on many wildlife species”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The report states that “ongoing disease surveillance programmes should be established to identify new and emerging pathogens”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;H5N1 spread almost 4,000 miles down South America in the space of three months, facilitated by migration routes of wild birds. The fact it had already spread down South America made it likely it would arrive in South Georgia at some point, researchers say.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As a result of the positive tests on Bird Island, most field work that involves animal handling has been suspended. Staff will have to be extra vigilant about ensuring they have clean clothing and field equipment.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The news follows recent research that showed some seabirds in the UK – where the outbreak was first reported – are starting &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/oct/20/wild-birds-gain-immunity-to-avian-flu-in-encouraging-sign-amid-deadly-outbreak&quot;>;to show immunity&lt;/a>; to H5N1.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 24 Oct 2023 23:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Australia approved 322 defence exports to Israel in six years as Greens fear equipment used in Gaza assault]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/24/australia-approved-322-defence-exports-to-israel-in-six-years-as-greens-fear-equipment-used-in-gaza-assault]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-10-24T14:00:40Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/701853fa1af90fcc4b31a596ac897e54baa26435/0_135_2048_1229/master/2048.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=3ab26ccbf48ac139b11c200defa52a6f&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Australia and Israel flags&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Australia has approved 322 defence exports to Israel over the past six years, according to new figures that will fuel questions at a Senate hearing on Wednesday.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The government-compiled figures, which include 49 permits for Israel-bound exports last year and 23 in the first three months of this year, may cover both military-specific goods and also dual-use devices.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Greens&#39; defence spokesperson, David Shoebridge, said Australia had “one of the most secretive and unaccountable weapons export systems in the world”, given that it doesn&#39;t break down the exact items exported.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/oct/24/dfat-urged-stronger-israeli-settlements-stance-that-coalition-claimed-factional-bosses-were-behind&quot;>;Dfat urged stronger Israeli settlements stance that Coalition claimed &#39;factional bosses&#39; were behind&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Shoebridge, who will ask the defence department about the exports at a Senate estimates hearing in Canberra on Wednesday, said he held “a very deep concern that Australian material is being used in the attack on Gaza”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;However, the figures do not go into that level of detail. In response to questions on notice from Shoebridge, the government disclosed that 322 permits for Israel-bound military or dual-use exports had been issued since 1 January 2017.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The number of permits for Israel peaked at 62 in 2021, before dropping to 49 in 2022, followed by a further 23 in January to March this year.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Israel was one of 14 countries for which Shoebridge sought defence export figures. The Philippines was the second-largest destination among the countries that were part of the question, with 158 permits in the same period.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Other destinations included Mali (70 permits) and Burkina Faso (56 permits).&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/05/australias-rise-in-military-export-approvals-to-saudi-arabia-labelled-disturbing&quot;>;Previous disclosures indicated&lt;/a>; that Australia approved 21 permits for the export of military or dual-use equipment to Saudi Arabia between 1 January and 9 November 2022, an increase on previous levels to that country.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In the response detailing the figures, the government said permits were “required for a broad range of goods and technologies such as software, radios or chemicals that have legitimate civilian and commercial applications”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Every export permit decision must assess any relevant human rights risks and Australia&#39;s compliance with its international obligations,” the government response said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“If Defence identified an export might be used to facilitate human rights abuses, a permit would be refused.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The government said each export application was assessed against criteria that include foreign policy, human rights, national security, regional security and Australia&#39;s international obligations such as the Arms Trade Treaty.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;But the Greens argue Australia should join other countries in publishing “who we are selling weapons to, what those weapons are and how much they cost”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“When Australia changed governments last year there was hope it would reverse the Coalition&#39;s push to make Australia a top 10 global arms dealer,” Shoebridge said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Instead, the Albanese government has doubled down on arms sales to some of the world&#39;s most troubling regimes.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Last week a &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/oct/19/state-department-official-josh-paul-quits-weapons-israel&quot;>;veteran US state department official quit his role&lt;/a>; in protest at arms sales to Israel, saying he had made many “moral compromises” during his 11 years at the Bureau of Political-Military Affairs.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Josh Paul said in &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7120512510645952512/&quot;>;a letter&lt;/a>; posted on LinkedIn that he had promised to stay in that role “for as long as I felt the harm I might do could be outweighed by the good I could do”.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2023/oct/16/australian-parliament-unites-to-condemn-hate-speech-including-antisemitism-and-islamophobia&quot;>;Australian parliament unites to condemn hate speech including antisemitism and Islamophobia&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“I am leaving today because I believe that in our current course with regards to the continued – indeed, expanded and expedited – provision of lethal arms to Israel, I have reached the end of that bargain,” Paul wrote.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The US &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/oct/23/pentagon-military-advisers-air-defense-israel-hamas-war-gaza&quot;>;said this week &lt;/a>;it was sending military advisers and air defence systems to Israel ahead of an anticipated ground assault into Gaza by Israel&#39;s military.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Australian government has joined the US in affirming Israel&#39;s right to self-defence after the 7 October Hamas attack, but has also called for the protection of civilian lives and humanitarian access to Gaza.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Israeli ambassador to Australia, Amir Maimon, is due to speak about the war in an address in Canberra on Wednesday.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Tue, 24 Oct 2023 22:22:02 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>